The paper focuses on multicast in wireless networks, specifically using network coding to reduce bandwidth cost. This topic falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes new heuristics for selecting rates, which involves optimization and decision-making, making it relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the behavior and performance of the heuristics, which could be considered a form of simulation and modeling, making it relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
